news.title: Birla Estates to jointly develop 52-acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: The project has a revenue potential of Rs 3,000 crore and development potential 4 million sq ft and will comprise both high and low-rise residential developments, along with retail and commercial elements.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: CAG pitches for mandatory revision of property tax after every five years
news.para: The country’s top auditor also found several shortcomings in empowerment of urban local bodies and their functioning, financial management, fiscal autonomy, self-reliance, quality of expenditure, role of parastatals and human resources of the urban local bodies.

news.title: Narela flats offered in DDA Housing Scheme 2019 didn't get adequate response
news.para: "Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has informed that flats offered in Vasant Kunj under DDA Housing Scheme 2019 had received an overwhelming response. However the flats offered in Narela did not get the adequate response," the minister said, and shared block-wise break-up for the flats included in draw of lots and allotment for the same.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation's projected property income falls short of target
news.para: ​The rental income from civic properties for 2022-23 has been projected at Rs 9.33 crore. However, deputy mayor P K Raju himself revised the last year’s estimated income from 10 crore to Rs 7.95 crore.

news.title: Mahindra Holidays to invest Rs 1,200 crore over three years
news.para: ​“We are a cash rich company and we have seen the cash on our books go up from Rs 760 crore just before the pandemic to Rs 1,108 crore now so this ramp up will be funded through internal accruals entirely,” said Kavinder Singh, MD & CEO, Mahindra Holidays.

news.title: Bhopal panel okays hike in collector's guideline of properties
news.para: “Indore district-level evaluation committee had proposed a 10-25% hike at 745 locations including 127 schemes of Indore Development Authority after disposing of all 60 claims and objections received against it,” DIG registration (Indore region) Balkrishna More said.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Three illegal buildings in Digha to be razed soon
news.para: The illegal buildings in question include Kamlakar Apartment, Moreshwar Apartment and Bhagatji Apartment. Tenants were removed from the buildings four years ago, and the building was then sealed by the court for further action.

news.title: Over 19,000 properties sealed for non-payment of taxes in Ahmedabad
news.para: “We have sealed properties of those who have defaulted on property tax despite several notices. During this drive, the department has recovered pending tax totalling Rs 319 crore as on March 24,” said Jainik Vakil, chairman of Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation’s revenue committee.

news.title: Fire safety takes a back seat as many buildings in Hyderabad lack open area
news.para: While guidelines state that residential buildings not more than five floors and commercial buildings not more than three floors do not require NOC, even those who need it fail to apply for the same due to lack of open space.

news.title: Nashik civic body's property tax up 22% in current financial year
news.para: The civic body’s collection of property tax was severely affected during the previous fiscal due to the Covid pandemic. But various measures taken by the NMC — like amnesty scheme and issuance of warrants for confiscation of properties — led to adding Rs 24 core in the coffers of the civic body.

news.title: FIR against 51 for carving out illegal colonies in Sultanpur & Farrukhnagar
news.para: On the complaint of department of town and country planning (DTCP), 10 FIRs have been lodged against the offenders who were developing 10 illegal colonies ranging from two to eight acres on prime agricultural land.

news.title: Noida: Residential projects will get OCs after environmental experts' nod
news.para: In fact, the Noida Authority has already shortlisted two firms for hiring environmental experts for overseeing compliance with the NGT norms.

news.title: Errors in property IDs? Walk into Gurugram civic body camps to fix them
news.para: While some residents complained that their properties are shown in their neighbour’s name, some said their house numbers in the new property ID are wrong. Some residents also claimed that they were unable to make the corrections online, and would therefore have to visit the MCG office to rectify the mistakes.

news.title: Cement prices rise just as demand grows
news.para: According to various brokerage reports, based on dealer interactions, the pan India average cement price rose by over 10% to Rs 395 per 50 kg bag as of March 22, 2022, on a month-on-month basis. It grew by 11% based on the year-on-year comparison.

news.title: Gurugram: Architects, engineers could face FIRs for building flaws
news.para: The move comes against the backdrop of the vertical collapse of living rooms at Chintels Paradiso that claimed two lives on February 10. Residents there had for long raised questions on the structural safety of buildings.
